chefs.bio: Chef Alice Johnson has a passion for blending the bold flavors of Asian cuisine with modern cooking techniques. Her dishes are known for their vibrant colors, bold spices, and fresh ingredients.

recipes.ingredients: 1 lb chicken breast, sliced thinly, 1 onion, sliced, red bell pepper, sliced, 1 green bell pepper, sliced, 2 cloves garlic, minced
recipes.cooking_method: In a large skillet or wok, heat oil over high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned, about 5-7 minutes. Remove chicken from skillet and set aside. Add onion and peppers to skillet and cook until tender-crisp, about 3-4 minutes. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Return chicken to skillet and stir to combine. Serve hot with tortillas and toppings of your choice.
